Sentencas: Fuel sensitivity experiments form an important feature of testing solid oxide fuel cell systems.

Sentencas: In this paper we describe a fuel sensitivity test and its relation to fuel utilization.

Sentencas: The sensitivity of the measured terminal voltage of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell to the fuel utilization provides important information about 'leaks' through the cell.

Sentencas: Such leaks could arise from pinholes in the electrolyte or from other sources.

Sentencas: First a simple analytical model is presented which is then refined using a numerical simulation.
